# Project Structure

LocalCA-Go is organized into a Go backend and a Next.js frontend, with a clear separation of concerns.

## Directory Structure

- [main.go](mdc:main.go) - Application entry point
- [pkg/](mdc:pkg) - Core Go packages
  - [certificates/](mdc:pkg/certificates) - Certificate operations
  - [config/](mdc:pkg/config) - Configuration management
  - [storage/](mdc:pkg/storage) - Certificate storage
  - [handlers/](mdc:pkg/handlers) - HTTP handlers
  - [email/](mdc:pkg/email) - Email notifications
  - [acme/](mdc:pkg/acme) - ACME protocol implementation
- [app/](mdc:app) - Next.js frontend
  - [page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) - Main dashboard
  - [create/](mdc:app/create) - Certificate creation
  - [certificates/](mdc:app/certificates) - Certificate management
  - [settings/](mdc:app/settings) - Application settings
  - [api/](mdc:app/api) - API routes
- [components/](mdc:components) - React components
- [data/](mdc:data) - Data access layer
- [styles/](mdc:styles) - CSS and styling
- [public/](mdc:public) - Static assets
- [docker-compose.yml](mdc:docker-compose.yml) - Docker configuration

## Key Files

- [go.mod](mdc:go.mod) - Go dependencies
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Frontend dependencies
- [next.config.mjs](mdc:next.config.mjs) - Next.js configuration
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind CSS configuration
- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Project documentation
- [DEPLOYMENT.md](mdc:DEPLOYMENT.md) - Deployment instructions
